      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "Language model basically understands the underlying language itself.",
      "start_time": 369.56,
      "end_time": 372.6,
      "language": "en",
      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "Say for example, if I'm speaking in English,",
      "start_time": 372.64,
      "end_time": 375.68,
      "language": "en",
      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "understanding my voice is one part,",
      "start_time": 376.48,
      "end_time": 378.72,
      "language": "en",
      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "but understanding English itself is another part.",
      "start_time": 379.22,
      "end_time": 382.1,
      "language": "en",
      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "English also has a lot of grammar in it.",
      "start_time": 382.42,
      "end_time": 384.58,
      "language": "en",
      "confidence": -0.08645622780982484
    },
    {
      "text": "So if we understand the English language and the grammar behind it,",
